NAME
    du - estimate file space usage

SYNOPSIS
    du [options] [file...]

DESCRIPTION
    Summarizes disk usage for each file and directory,
    recursively for directories.

OPTIONS
    -a              Show all files, not just directories
    -h              Human-readable sizes (1K, 2M, 3G)
    -s              Display only total for each argument
    -c              Produce a grand total
    -d <depth>      Max depth to display
    --max-depth=<n> Same as -d
    -b              Show sizes in bytes
    -k              Show sizes in kilobytes (default)
    -m              Show sizes in megabytes

EXAMPLES
    du
        Show current directory usage

    du -sh /api/data
        4.5M    /api/data

    du -ah /tmp
        Show all files with human sizes

    du -d 1 /
        Show only one level deep

    du -sc /api/data /home
        Summary for each with grand total

    du -b file.txt
        Exact byte count

OUTPUT
    SIZE    PATH

    Size is in 1K blocks by default.

SEE ALSO
    df, ls, find
